# React Native Guidelines

## Platform Detection
```tsx
import { Platform } from 'react-native';

// Conditional rendering
{Platform.OS === 'ios' && <IOSOnlyComponent />}

// Conditional styles
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    padding: 16,
    ...Platform.select({
      ios: { paddingTop: 20 },
      android: { paddingTop: 10 },
      web: { paddingTop: 0 },
    }),
  },
});
```

## Safe Areas
- ALWAYS wrap apps in SafeAreaView
- Test on the latest iphone device (iPhone 17+)
- Account for home indicator on bottom

## Responsive Design
```tsx
import { useWindowDimensions } from 'react-native';

const { width } = useWindowDimensions();
const isMobile = width < 768;
```

## Touch Targets
- Minimum: 44x44 points on iOS
- Minimum: 48x48 dp on Android
- Test on actual devices, not just simulator

## Images & Assets
- Use expo-asset for web compatibility
- Provide @2x and @3x variants
- Optimize images before committing

## Fonts
- Web: Load via document.createElement('style')
- Native: Use system fonts or expo-font
- Always provide fallbacks
